rComments: Clearly a good looking professor. However, she is not that competent in her critical thinking and is very closed-minded.

completely agree with the post below. Psy300 is the worst and most useless psych course I have taken to date. That said, Iserman is good prof. Clear, helpful, and funny. Too bad she teaches such an awful course...

Most helpful instructor I've ever had. Makes herself available to students as best as she can, very clear lectures and she's always happy and welcoming to any questions. Tests are very fair, consisting of lectures and textbook material so if you study, you'll do well. Her lectures are very well organized, interesting & communicated with enthusiasm.
Nice professor who teaches well, but she seems pretty bitter about her lecturer status. Must read the textbook to do well on the tests!

A good prof. very approachable, with a dry sense of humor. The tests were 25-50% **** that has nothing to do with understanding the history of psychology. So if enjoy memorizing a myriad of completely useless and irrelevant facts about the personal lives of old dead white men then you'll love this course and I completely recommend you take it.
